'''Requínoa''' ({{IPA-es|reˈkinoa}}) is a [[Chile]]an [[Communes of Chile|commune]] and [[List of cities in Chile|city]] in [[Cachapoal Province]], [[O'Higgins Region]].
==Demographics== According to the 2002 [[census]] of the [[National Statistics Institute (Chile)|National Statistics Institute]], Requínoa spans an area of {{convert|673.3|sqkm|0|abbr=on}} and had 22,161 inhabitants (11,378 men and 10,783 women). Of these, 11,167 (50.4%) lived in [[urban area]]s and 10,994 (49.6%) in [[rural area]]s. The population grew by 14% (2,729 persons) between the 1992 and 2002 censuses.<ref name= "INE"/> The 2012 census reported 26,089 inhabitants, an increase of 17.7% from 2002 to 2012.<ref name="Censo-2012">Codigo 6116, Requínoa, {{Cite web |author=Comisión Externa Revisora del Censo 2012 |title=Anexo 1. Población Reportada a Nivel Comunal |work=Al Informe Final: Anexos |date=August 2013|language=es |publisher= National Statistics Institute (INE) |page=41 |url= http://www.ine.cl/canales/chile_estadistico/censos_poblacion_vivienda/comision_investigadora/nacional/anexos_comision_externa_revisora-comision-nacional.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141203004548/http://www.ine.cl/canales/chile_estadistico/censos_poblacion_vivienda/comision_investigadora/nacional/anexos_comision_externa_revisora-comision-nacional.pdf |archivedate=3 December 2014}}</ref>
==Administration== As a commune, Requínoa is a third-level [[administrative division of Chile]] administered by a [[municipal council]], headed by an [[alcalde]] who is directly elected every four years. The 2008-2012 alcalde is Antonio Silva Vargas ([[Independent (politician)|Ind.]]). The council has the following members:<ref name="Official"/> * Daniel Elías Martínez Higueras ([[Socialist Party of Chile|PS]]) * María Eliana Berríos Bustos (ILE) * Rolando Andrés Guajardo Arévalo (ILC) * Hugo Alejandro Núñez Guerrero ([[Independent Democratic Union|UDI]]) * Sergio Cabezas Díaz ([[National Renewal (Chile)|RN]]) * Francisco Odeón Caro Godoy ([[Independent (politician)|Ind.]])
Within the [[electoral divisions of Chile]], Requínoa is represented in the [[Chamber of Deputies of Chile|Chamber of Deputies]] by Mr. Eugenio Bauer ([[Independent Democratic Union|UDI]]) and Mr. Ricardo Rincón ([[Christian Democratic Party|PDC]]) as part of the 33rd electoral district, (together with [[Mostazal]], [[Graneros]], [[Codegua]], [[Machalí]], [[Rengo]], [[El Olivar, Chile|Olivar]], [[Doñihue]], [[Coínco|Coinco]], [[Coltauco]], [[Quinta de Tilcoco]] and [[Malloa]]). The commune is represented in the [[Senate of Chile|Senate]] by Andrés Chadwick Piñera (UDI) and Juan Pablo Letelier Morel ([[Socialist Party of Chile|PS]]) as part of the 9th senatorial constituency (O'Higgins Region).
